title: Rab and his friends and other dogs and men,
author: Brown, John
snippet: It was less than three hours since he left, and he must have posted out who knows how ? to Howgate, full nine miles off ; yoked Jess, and driven her astonished into town.

title: Rab and his friends and other dogs and men,
author: Brown, John
snippet: Jess, the mare, had been sent, with her weatherworn  cart, to Howgate, and had doubtless her own dim and placid meditations and confusions, on the absence of her master and Rab, and her unnatural freedom from the road and her cart.
